what are the privacy issues related to wearable technologies
1. the government has accses to all of the data the watch would collect like heart rate location amount of sleep stress levels blood oxygen levels and how many steps you have walked / how far you have walked 
2. the government can have accsess to all of those records without having your consent


wearables for atheletes 
advantages 
better performance 
better medical care results in fewer injurues or fast recovery from injury
feedback from coaches is more focused 
improved kits are more comfortable and more efficient 
part of a team not isolated

diadvantages

invades privacy 
blurs lines between personal and proffesional time
avalability and cost
temps atheleats / coaches into cheating or unfair practices
puts sole focus on winning and not athletic endeavor
